<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-6618] NullPointerException while stopping/draining if native transport wasn&apos;t started</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6618</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;if using a custom Authenticator, native transport server wouldn&apos;t be started.&lt;br/&gt;
ERROR &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;main&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; 2014-01-24 03:04:40,876 Server.java (line 131) Not starting native transport as the configured IAuthenticator is not capable of SASL authentication&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, while stopping cassandra/&apos;nodetool drain&apos;, this results in NullpointerException being thrown currently:&lt;br/&gt;
Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
