                            <comment id="13881386" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 20:25:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was already fixed in 0d38b25f6fa3b&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881451" author="ravilr" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 21:45:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;nativeServer.isRunning could be set to true, even when it wasn&apos;t started due to custom authenticator not supporting sasl.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881452" author="ravilr" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 21:46:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brandon, there still seems to be a logic error, which could wrongly set nativeServer.isRunning to true, even when it wasn&apos;t started. Can you please check.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881470" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 22:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t see how setting it to true after calling run() or calling it as the last step inside run() makes any difference.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881517" author="ravilr" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 23:00:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;if the authenticator is not Saslaware, the run() returns without starting the nativeServer and we still set isRunning to true, in that case:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/transport/Server.java#L133&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/cassandra-2.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/transport/Server.java#L133&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881520" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 23:05:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see, I was looking at 1.2.  Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
